      h3.headline-4 Key Infrastructure
      p Datica’s private key infrastructure ensures that your data is protected and can only be accessed by those with appropriate permission.
      ul
        li You have the option to either provide your own Root CA, or rely on Datica to create and store one for you.
        li Once the Root CA is established, Datica creates an intermediate CA.
        li This intermediate CA is used for generating all cluster specific certs. 
    .column
      svg.icon-tone.icon-size--large
        use.solid xlink:href="#shield-half" 
      h3.headline-4 Compliance Artifact Storage
      p Once your Kubernetes<sup>&reg;</sup> cluster is installed and configured, Datica will store compliance artifact data.
      ul
        li Our logging stack ties directly into the compliance artifact storage.
        li Certain compliance data must be relayed back to Datica’s centrally managed Cloud Compliance Management System for processing.
        li The Compliance Artifact Storage mechanism is the lifeblood of the Cloud Compliance Management System.
    .column
      svg.icon-tone.icon-size--large
        use.solid xlink:href="#state-box" 
      h3.headline-4 Continuous Compliance Engine
      p The core value of the Datica Cloud Compliance Management System is that we are continuously ensuring the complete compliance of both your cluster, and the underlying infrastructure that it resides on.
      ul
        li We do this by comparing the running state with the expected compliance state.
        li When anomalies and events are detected, a Datica Security and Compliance expert will review the logs and take necessary steps.
    .column
      svg.icon-tone.icon-size--large
        use.solid xlink:href="#icon-dashboard" 
